Technological feasibility: High (70-85% in the next 3-5 years)
What already exists:
Federated learning is a technology in which an AI model is trained on the user's device, and only parameter updates, not raw data, are transmitted to the server. Google uses this in Gboard, Apple to improve Siri.

Personal foundation models: Research shows that local AI adaptation to the user is possible without transmitting personal data to the cloud.

Encoder-decoder architecture: A proposed design involves an "encoder" on a wearable device compressing input signals into latent representations, which are then processed on the smartphone. Raw audio/video never leaves the device.

